ing and updating new plugins all the time, which might confuse you further. This guide will steer you [&#8230;]<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/5-latest-wordpress-plugins-to-boost-your-blogs-activity/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"ericalsunarjo\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11393:\"<p style=\"display: block; padding: 0 0 24px; margin: 0 !important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/5-latest-wordpress-plugins-to-boost-your-blogs-activity/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/featured_image_3_plugins_wordpress_membership-1200x600.jpg\" width=\"1200\" height=\"600\" title=\"5 Latest WordPress Plugins To Boost Your Blog&#8217;s Activity\" alt=\"5 Latest WordPress Plugins To Boost Your Blog&#8217;s Activity\" style=\"width: 100%!important;\"></a></p><p style=\"padding: 0 26px !important; margin: 0 !important;\"><p style=\"text-align: justify\">There is a dazzling array of WordPress plugins out there. How do you know which to choose for your blog? If you have recently set up your site, you may feel overwhelmed by your options. Developers are releasing and updating new plugins all the time, which might confuse you further.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">This guide will steer you in the right direction. Let’s look at five plugins that will rocket your blog to success.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><strong>Five WordPress Plugins You Will Love</strong></p>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify\">\n<li><strong><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/extension/ocean-cookie-notice/\">Ocean Cookie Notice for GDPR</a></strong></li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-270399 alignleft\" src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cookie-notice-image-300x144.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"144\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cookie-notice-image-300x144.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cookie-notice-image-768x369.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cookie-notice-image.png 833w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />The laws surrounding data collection has changed in 2018. The GDPR, a key piece of EU legislation, is now in full effect. In brief, it has significant implications for the way site owners and bloggers collect visitor information.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">To comply with the GDPR, you need to place a notification on your site. However, these rules are quite complicated. Writing your own popup is risky. If you do not comply with the rules, you risk incurring a heavy fine. What’s more, clumsy notifications might annoy your visitors, driving them away from your site.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/extension/ocean-cookie-notice/\">Ocean Cookie Notice for GDPR</a> solves this problem by letting you set up stylish, fully compliant notices on your site. You won’t have to worry about falling foul of the law or irritating your readers.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Key Takeaway: This plugin will improve user experience by presenting visitors with attractive legal notifications.</em></p>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify\" start=\"2\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/autodescription/#description\"><strong> The SEO Framework</strong></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-267678 size-medium\" src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/banner-4096x2151-300x158.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"158\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/banner-4096x2151-300x158.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/banner-4096x2151-768x403.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/banner-4096x2151-1024x538.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />To attract search engine traffic, you need to optimize your blog for discovery by search engines. If you are new to SEO, the amount of information online might seem bewildering. Working with an SEO professional can be expensive. Fortunately, there are lots of plugins that help you do it yourself.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/autodescription/#description\">The SEO Framework</a> offers an easy solution. It’s a free plugin that helps you optimize every single part of your blog. You can optimize pages and even individual blog posts. If you want to attract visitors from around the world, you’ll love the global SEO feature.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Key Takeaway: This plugin will attract more visitors to your site by managing your SEO, thereby helping you rank higher in search engines.</em></p>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify\" start=\"3\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\"><strong> WP Rocket</strong></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-267679 size-medium\" src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/logo-dark-300x81.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"81\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/logo-dark-300x81.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/logo-dark-768x209.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/logo-dark.png 950w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />No one likes to wait around for a webpage to load. The <a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\">WP Rocket</a> plugin boosts your blog’s speed within minutes of installation. <a href=\"https://wp-rocket.me/\">Over 500,000 people use it</a> to improve their site’s loading time.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">It increases your blog’s speed in a several ways. First, your images are loaded only if a visitor scrolls down the page, saving space. The plugin minifies CSS, HTML, and JavaScript files for a faster browsing experience. Its page caching feature is activated upon launch and is simple to configure.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Finally, the plugin offers developers great customization potential. If you are a more advanced user, you will appreciate its clean code.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Key Takeaway: This plugin will make your site faster, meaning your readers will stick around for longer. </em></p>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify\" start=\"4\">\n<li><a href=\"https://codecanyon.net/item/easy-social-share-buttons-for-wordpress/6394476?ref=athemez&amp;clickthrough_id=1387710893&amp;redirect_back=true\"><strong>Easy Social Share Buttons for WordPress</strong></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-270496 alignleft\" src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cc-new-image55-02-300x153.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"153\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cc-new-image55-02-300x153.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/cc-new-image55-02.png 590w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />Likes and shares on social media can extend your outreach and win you thousands of new readers. <a href=\"https://codecanyon.net/item/easy-social-share-buttons-for-wordpress/6394476?ref=athemez&amp;clickthrough_id=1387710893&amp;redirect_back=true\">Easy Social Share Buttons for WordPress</a> let readers share your blog on over 50 social networks.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">The plugin allows you to quickly set up sharing buttons and social media counters that invite reader engagement. It comes with over 50 templates and over 30 sharing animations. You can go one step further and set up live Facebook or Skype chat for a more immersive experience.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">It’s a good idea to analyze your content’s performance. This plugin makes it easy to track what kind of content works best. This allows you to shape your blog strategy and build an audience.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">As a bonus, you can also use this plugin to build a mailing list. It is fully GDPR compliant, so you don’t need to worry about mishandling subscribers’ data.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Key Takeaway: This plugin will make it easy for visitors to share your content. When more people view your posts on social media, you will see more traffic to your site.</em></p>\n<ol style=\"text-align: justify\" start=\"5\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/geolocated-content/\"><strong> Geolocated Content</strong></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-267681 size-medium\" src=\"https://oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screenshot_1-300x134.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"134\" srcset=\"//oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screenshot_1-300x134.png 300w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screenshot_1-768x342.png 768w, //oceanwp.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screenshot_1.png 942w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" />If you blog for people in multiple countries, you should try this open source plugin. With a few clicks, you can configure your site to show different versions of your content, depending on where your visitor lives. The plugin uses the WordPress public geo API to detect their location.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">This means you can tailor your content to several markets. For example, if you publish a fashion blog, you might want to talk about trends specific to various regions.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">If you sell products and services via your site, this plugin will help you localize your marketing strategy. However, you can also choose to show same content to all visitors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Be sure to check that your content is translated perfectly before publishing it. Always use a trustworthy translation service such as <a href=\"https://thewordpoint.com/\">The Word Point</a>. This plugin does translate text.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em>Key Takeaway: This plugin is a great option if your blog serves an international audience. </em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><strong>How To Pick The Right Plugin</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">The perfect plugin for your blog depends on many factors, including but not limited to:</p>\n<ul style=\"text-align: justify\">\n<li>Whether you sell products or services from your blog</li>\n<li>Your blog’s design and tone</li>\n<li>Your blog’s topic</li>\n<li>The location and preferences of your target audience</li>\n<li>Whether you want and need additional customization</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Take care not to overload your site with plugins. This can slow performance and leave visitors frustrated. Be willing to experiment. If a plugin doesn’t suit your blog, try another.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Reading the reviews on WordPress.org can also help you make the right choice. If you have any questions about the purpose and function of a plugin, you can also try getting in touch with the developer. Remember to keep plugins updated, and delete those you no longer use.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><strong>Conclusion</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">You can use plugins to build a blog that perfectly fits your tastes. However, you must take your visitors’ needs into account. After all, if they find your blog difficult to navigate, it’s unlikely they will return. When you make major changes, as them for some honest feedback. The better their experience, the more successful your site will be.</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0!important;padding: 26px 0 0!important;\"><a href=\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/5-latest-wordpress-plugins-to-boost-your-blogs-activity/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"display: inline-block; padding: 10px 30px; color: #ffffff; background-color: #13aff0; border-radius: 30px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.4; text-transform: uppercase; text-align: center; text-decoration: none; letter-spacing: 1px;\">Read More</a></p></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/5-latest-wordpress-plugins-to-boost-your-blogs-activity/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"How to Optimize Your WordPress Site for Conversions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"https://oceanwp.org/blog/how-to-optimize-your-wordpress-site-for-conversions/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"https